        pricing_overview: '<p>Photor operates on a heavily Freemium or low-cost transactional model. Users can generally upload a limited number of photos (e.g., testing 5 headshots) entirely for free. A premium upgrade or one-time payment is usually required to unlock massive batch testing (scanning an entire camera roll), deeper analytical insights, or priority processing.</p>',
        comparison_summary: '<p>Photor.io competes against crowdsourced human feedback platforms like Photofeeler, and generative enhancement tools like Remini. Photofeeler relies on actual human beings voting on your photo, which provides genuine societal feedback but takes hours or days to collect statistically significant data. Remini attempts to actively make you look better by altering the pixels. Photor differentiates itself as the ultimate *Instant Objective Oracle*. It sacrifices the nuance of human opinion for the sheer speed of algorithmic certainty, giving you a definitive, mathematical answer on which photo to use in 5 seconds.</p>'
