        pricing_overview: '<p>Pixlr operates on a high-volume Freemium model. The basic editor is accessible for free, supported heavily by display ads and restricting access to premium AI features or high-resolution exports. Premium subscription tiers (Plus and Premium) remove the ads, unlock the full generative AI suite with dedicated prompt credits, and provide access to massive libraries of fonts, templates, and stock assets.</p>',
        comparison_summary: '<p>Pixlr competes in a brutal, crowded space against Canva and Adobe Express. Canva is the undisputed king of template-driven graphic design and layout. Adobe Express leverages the immense power of Adobe Firefly AI. Pixlr differentiates itself by remaining true to its roots as a *Photo Editor First*. While Canva is a layout tool where you place photos, Pixlr is a canvas where you surgically edit the pixels of the photo itself using AI, maintaining the granular feel of Photoshop in a fast, cheap browser tab.</p>'
